on (Twentieth Century) -- tV Contemporary Contexts -- t19 Historiography and Literary Essays on Latin American Jews in the New Millennium -- t20 Contemporary Jewish Narrative in Twentyfirst Century Latin America -- t21 Writing Cuban Belonging through Jewish Eyes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume offers a thorough introduction to Jewish world literatures in Spanish and Portuguese, which not only addresses the coexistence of cultures, but also the functions of a literary and linguistic space of negotiation in this context. From the Middle Ages to present day, the compendium explores the main Jewish chapters within Spanish- and Portuguese-language world literature, whether from Europe, Latin America, or other parts of the world. No comprehensive survey of this area has been undertaken so far. Yet only a broad focus of this kind can show how diasporic Jewish literatures have been (and are ) – while closely tied to their own traditions – deeply intertwined with local and global literary developments; and how the aesthetic praxis they introduced played a decisive, formative role in the history of literature. With this epistemic claim, the volume aims at steering clear of isolationist approaches to Jewish literatures.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aComparative Literature.  aCultural History.  aJewish Studies.  aRomance Literary Studies.1 aAmrán, Rica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBejarano, Margalit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoer, Harm den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBossong, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4http